# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CLOUDFLARE WORKER secrets — for LOCAL `wrangler dev` only.
# Copy to `newsletter/worker/.dev.vars` (gitignored) and fill in.
#
# In PRODUCTION these are NOT files — push each one with:
#     npx wrangler secret put <NAME>
# (run from newsletter/worker/). Never commit real values.
#
# Non-secret config (DATA_REPO, MAIL_FROM_*, WORKER_PUBLIC_URL, …) is NOT here —
# it lives in wrangler.toml [vars].
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Data-repo access. Fine-grained GitHub PAT, scoped to the private data repo,
# Contents: Read and write. (Same token used as the NEWSLETTER_DATA_TOKEN
# GitHub Actions secret.)
#   prod: npx wrangler secret put GITHUB_TOKEN
GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_xxx

# Email provider API key (current provider: Brevo).
# Where: Brevo → SMTP & API → API Keys (a transactional key).
#   prod: npx wrangler secret put BREVO_API_KEY
BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-xxx

# Cloudflare Turnstile **Secret Key** (the PRIVATE half of the key pair).
# Where: Cloudflare dashboard → Turnstile → your widget → "Secret Key".
# This is the counterpart of PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITEKEY (which lives in the SITE
# .env). Keep it secret — it must never reach the browser.
#   prod: npx wrangler secret put TURNSTILE_SECRET
# Optional locally: if unset, the Worker skips challenge verification. To test
# the real path, use Cloudflare's always-pass test secret:
#   1x0000000000000000000000000000000AA
TURNSTILE_SECRET=
